  "body": "I made a public custom eth2 testnet.\r\nSo anyone can connect to my node to make a transaction in my network, and also I can use MetaMask for transaction and keep tokens.\r\nHowever It's running with only one Node(Machine1) and 64 Validators, I just want to participate more node to my network to test.\r\n\r\nBut finding Network? Peer? is not working, I tried almost same command for GETH, BEACON-CHAIN when I run machine2.\r\nHow can I make machine2 automatically connect to machine1's network?\r\nOr\r\nHow to make machine2's execution clinet make it syncing to machine1?\r\n\r\nmachine1 is running well at the moment\r\n\r\n```\r\n// machine 1 geth, beacon-chain commands\r\n./geth --port 30303 --networkid 142536 --http --http.api eth,net,web3,engine,admin --http.addr \"0.0.0.0\" --http.port 8545 --http.corsdomain \"\" --http.vhosts \"\" --ws --ws.api eth,net,web3,engine,admin --ws.addr \"0.0.0.0\" --ws.port 8546 --authrpc.jwtsecret jwt.hex --datadir gethdata --syncmode full --allow-insecure-unlock --unlock $pubkey1\r\n\r\n./beacon-chain --datadir beacondata --min-sync-peers 0 --genesis-state genesis.ssz --bootstrap-node= --interop-eth1data-votes --chain-config-file config.yml --contract-deployment-block 0 --chain-id 142536 --accept-terms-of-use --jwt-secret jwt.hex --suggested-fee-recipient  $pubkey1 --minimum-peers-per-subnet 0 --enable-debug-rpc-endpoints --execution-endpoint gethdata/geth.ipc\r\n```\r\n\r\nmachine2' geth keep looking for peers and beacon-chain can't connect to network\r\n\r\n```\r\n// machine 2 geth, beacon-chain commands\r\n./geth --port 30304 --networkid 142536 --http --http.api eth,net,web3,engine,admin --http.addr \"0.0.0.0\" --http.port 8545 --http.corsdomain \"\" --http.vhosts \"\" --ws --ws.api eth,net,web3,engine,admin --ws.addr \"0.0.0.0\" --ws.port 8546 --authrpc.jwtsecret jwt.hex --datadir gethdata --syncmode full --allow-insecure-unlock --unlock  $pubkey2\r\n\r\n./beacon-chain --datadir beacondata --min-sync-peers 0 --genesis-state genesis.ssz --bootstrap-node= --interop-eth1data-votes --chain-config-file config.yml --contract-deployment-block 0 --chain-id 142536 --accept-terms-of-use --jwt-secret jwt.hex --suggested-fee-recipient $pubkey2 --minimum-peers-per-subnet 0 --enable-debug-rpc-endpoints --execution-endpoint gethdata/geth.ipc\r\n```\r\n\r\nSome more information\r\n1. They are using same genesis.json, genesis.ssz files and different jwt.hex file\r\n2. I'm controlling those 2 machines by my laptop which is connected to another wifi router. \r\n3. Both machine connected to same router and they got private ip.\r\n4. I did port forwardinf both machine's http and websocket, p2p(ex. 30303, 30304) port.\r\n5. Some Captures:\r\nGETH\r\n![image](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/assets/155970903/20d6dc04-cbc5-47ff-b67d-3c9ce4838e99)\r\n\r\nBEACON-CHAIN by Prysm\r\n![image](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/assets/155970903/4952c27d-a5ed-44c5-a288-b51b3f474f60)\r\n\r\n",
