    "body": "I believe you can set up a bootnode so that it's easier for your nodes to discover each other.\r\n\r\nOr the other straightforward way is to use `StaticNodes`. Here's how:\r\n\r\n1. Create a config.toml file with the following content:\r\n```\r\n[Node.P2P]\r\nStaticNodes = [<enode1>, <enode2>, ...]\r\n``` \r\n\r\n2. Add `--config config.toml` to your geth startup command\r\n\r\nLearn more about static nodes [here](https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/fundamentals/peer-to-peer#static-nodes).",
